1282","1170":"1170","Windermere, Westmorland, England":"Windermere, Westmorland, England","Leicestershire, England":"Leicestershire, England, United Kingdom","West Riding, Yorkshire, England":"Yorkshire, England, United Kingdom","Windermere, Westmorland, England, United Kingdom":"Windermere, Westmorland, England, United Kingdom","nameMeanings":[{"name":"Julianna","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Modern combination of the given names   Julie   and   Anna  , perhaps sometimes intended as a form of   Juliana ."],"variants":[]},{"name":"de","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Short form of the various boys' names with the first syllable <i>Ed-</i>, especially   Edward ."],"variants":[{"name":"Edward","meanings":["From an Old English personal name derived from <i>ēad</i> ‘prosperity, riches’ + <i>weard</i> ‘guard’. This has been one of the most successful of all Old English names, in frequent use from before the Conquest to the present day, and even being exported into other European languages. It was the name of three Anglo-Saxon kings and has been borne by eight kings of England since the Norman Conquest. It is also the name of the youngest son of  Queen Elizabeth II . The most influential early bearer was  King Edward  the Confessor (  ?1002–66 ; ruled  1042–66 ). In a troubled period of English history, he contrived to rule fairly and (for a time at any rate) firmly. But in the latter part of his reign he paid more attention to his religion than to his kingdom. He died childless, and his death sparked off conflicting claims to his throne, which were resolved by the victory of William the Conqueror at the Battle of Hastings. His memory was honoured by Normans and English alike, for his fairness and his piety. Edward's mother was Norman; he had spent part of his youth in Normandy; and William claimed to have been nominated by Edward as his successor. Edward was canonized in the 12th century, and came to be venerated throughout Europe as a model of a Christian king."]}]}],"historicEvents":[{"id":1705189,"age":25,"year":"1259","julianDay":2180901,"title":"100 Years of Conflict Between England and France Ends","description":"Treaty of Paris was signed on December 4, 1259, which ended 100 years of conflict between England and France.","url":"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Treaty_of_Paris_(1259)","urlTitle":"Wikipedia - Treaty of Paris 1259","jurisdictionLevel":2}],"lifeSummary":"Julianna de Birthwaite was born in 1234, in Windermere, Westmorland, England as the daughter of Peter De Birthwaite and Elizabeth. She had at least 2 sons with Sir William de Rockley. She died in 1282, in Yorkshire, England, United Kingdom, at the age of 48."},"et":{"1234–1282":"1234–1282","1200–1282":"1200–1282","1200–1268":"1200–1268","1260–1323":"1260–1323","1263–Male":"1263–Surnud","1170–1230":"1170–1230","–Female":"Surnud","1259":"1259","1323":"1323","1268":"1268","1234":"1234","1200":"1200","about 1268":"umbes 1268","1263":"1263","1230":"1230","1260":"1260","1282":"1282","1170":"1170","Windermere, Westmorland, England":"Windermere, Westmorland, England","Leicestershire, England":"Leicestershire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","West Riding, Yorkshire, England":"Yorkshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Windermere, Westmorland, England, United Kingdom":"Windermere, Westmorland, Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"1234–1282":"1234–1282","1200–1282":"1200–1282","1200–1268":"1200–1268","1260–1323":"1260–1323","1263–Male":"1263–Kuollut","1170–1230":"1170–1230","–Female":"Kuollut","1259":"1259","1323":"1323","1268":"1268","1234":"1234","1200":"1200","about 1268":"noin 1268","1263":"1263","1230":"1230","1260":"1260","1282":"1282","1170":"1170","Windermere, Westmorland, England":"Windermere, Westmorland, England","Leicestershire, England":"Leicestershire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","West Ri